# Assets Investment Exposure Property Commercial Residential Amount

## identifier
de8716

## type
float

## definition
This is the value of the reporting party's investments that result in an exposure to residential commercial property.
     
Commercial residential property exposure is defined according to the nature of the risk. An exposure should be classified as commercial residential property risk, if the exposure is subject to the performance of the residential property market. This exposure does not include property used for the reporting party's own operational use.

## syntax
### xbrl
- balance=debit
- name=Assets.Investment.ExposurePropertyCommercialResidential.Amount
- classification=baf/bafpo/bafpo7.02.06
- period=instant
